# Chrome Extension (Manifest V3) Cursor Rules

## Architecture
- Use Manifest V3 (V2 is deprecated)
- Service Worker: background logic (replaces background pages)
- Content Scripts: inject into web pages
- Popup: extension popup UI (React/Vue/vanilla)
- Options Page: extension settings

## Manifest V3 Key Changes
- `service_worker` instead of `background.scripts`
- `action` instead of `browser_action`/`page_action`
- Use `chrome.scripting.executeScript()` instead of `tabs.executeScript()`
- Declarative net request (`declarativeNetRequest`) instead of `webRequest`

## Communication
- Use `chrome.runtime.sendMessage()` for popup ↔ service worker
- Use `chrome.tabs.sendMessage()` for service worker → content script
- Use `chrome.runtime.onMessage.addListener()` for receiving messages
- Use `chrome.storage.local` for persistent data (not localStorage)

## Security
- Use `content_security_policy` in manifest
- Minimize required permissions — request only what's needed
- Use `optional_permissions` for features not always needed
- Sanitize content from web pages before processing

## Development
- Use TypeScript for type safety
- Use webpack/vite for bundling
- Test in Chrome DevTools: `chrome://extensions` → Developer mode
- Use `chrome.runtime.getManifest()` to access manifest data

## Publishing
- Create compelling Chrome Web Store listing
- Include screenshots and promotional images
- Write clear privacy policy
- Respond to user reviews promptly
